.TH LE-VIBE 1 "2026" "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
le-vibe \- Lé Vibe launcher (managed Ollama + Code OSS editor)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B le-vibe
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ editor_args " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Launches the Lé Vibe session: optional product first\-run bootstrap,
starts a dedicated\-port \fBollama serve\fR, then your editor (defaults in
\fBle_vibe.launcher\fR: \fBLE_VIBE_EDITOR\fR if set, else \fB/usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium\fR,
else \fB/usr/bin/codium\fR, else \fBcodium\fR on \fBPATH\fR). On exit, stops the
managed Ollama process so GPU VRAM is released.
.PP
Product naming: Lé Vibe is not Microsoft Visual Studio Code; use Code \-
OSS / VSCodium\-class editors.
.PP
Primary CLI name is \fBlvibe\fR (same as this program). Open the current directory in the editor:
.B lvibe \.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-skip\-first\-run
Skip Phase 1 product bootstrap before opening the editor.
.TP
.BR \-\-force\-first\-run
Re\-run first\-run bootstrap even if complete.
.TP
.BI \-\-editor " cmd"
Editor binary (default: \fBLE_VIBE_EDITOR\fR, else \fB/usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium\fR,
\fB/usr/bin/codium\fR, or \fBcodium\fR on \fBPATH\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-port " N"
Managed Ollama port (default 11435).
.PP
When first\-run bootstrap fails: set \fBLE_VIBE_VERBOSE\fR for stderr detail; \fBlvibe logs\fR prints the path and a \fBtail \-f\fR reminder, or use \fBlvibe logs \-\-path\-only\fR / \fBlvibe logs \-\-tail\fR \fIN\fR (STEP 6 JSON Lines). See \fBle\-vibe/README.md\fR \fIFirst\-run (launcher)\fR and \fBPRODUCT_SPEC_SECTION8_EVIDENCE.md\fR §10.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lvibe sync-agent-skills
.RI [ workspace ]
Copy missing agent skill templates into \fB.lvibe/agents/<agent_id>/skill.md\fR (e.g. after upgrading the \fBle\-vibe\fR stack). \fIworkspace\fR defaults to the current directory; \fB.lvibe/\fR must already exist. Does not start Ollama or the editor.
.TP
.B lvibe open-welcome
.RI [ workspace ]
Open \fB.lvibe/WELCOME.md\fR (PRODUCT_SPEC §4) in the editor. \fIworkspace\fR defaults to the current directory; \fB.lvibe/\fR must already exist from a prior consent\-gated open. Does not start Ollama or first\-run bootstrap.
.TP
.B lvibe welcome
.RI [ \-\-text " " workspace ]
§4 welcome path or terminal text — STEP 4 / E3.
.TP
.B lvibe apply\-opening\-skip
.RI [ workspace ]
PM session skip hook — \fBdocs/SESSION_ORCHESTRATION_SPEC.md\fR STEP 2.
.TP
.B lvibe continue\-rules
.RI [ workspace ]
Continue workspace rules — \fBle_vibe.continue_workspace\fR (STEP 3 / E2).
.TP
.B lvibe hygiene
.RI [ hygiene_options ]
Validate \fB.lvibe/\fR manifest, session JSON, and chunk path refs — same as \fBpython3 \-m le_vibe.hygiene\fR and \fBlvibe\-hygiene\fR(1).
.TP
.B lvibe workspace\-governance
.RI [ \-C " dir " | \-\-json ]
Consent, cap, \fB.lvibe/\fR usage — \fBPRODUCT_SPEC\fR §5 STEP 15.
.TP
.B lvibe master\-orchestrator
.RI [ \-\-print | \-\-json ]
STEP 16 orchestrator paths / fenced prompt — \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR.
.TP
.B lvibe ai\-pilot\-continue
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json ]
STEP 17 AI Pilot / Continue paths — \fBdocs/AI_PILOT_AND_CONTINUE.md\fR.
.TP
.B lvibe logs
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-tail " N " | \-\-json ]
With no flags: path and \fBtail \-f\fR reminder; else path only, last \fIN\fR lines, or JSON (\fBdocs/privacy\-and\-telemetry.md\fR).
.TP
.B lvibe continue-pin
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-json ]
Continue Open VSX pin — \fBdocs/continue\-extension\-pin.md\fR; \fBLE_VIBE_CONTINUE_PIN_FILE\fR overrides the pin file path.
.TP
.B lvibe verify-checksums
.RI [ \-C " dir " | \-\-json ]
Verify \fBSHA256SUMS\fR with \fBsha256sum \-c\fR; \fB\-\-json\fR for paths and captured output — \fBdocs/apt\-repo\-releases.md\fR (H1).
.TP
.B lvibe pip-audit
.RI [ \-\-json | pip\-audit_options ]
Supply\-chain audit via \fBpip\-audit\fR; \fB\-\-json\fR for paths and captured output — \fBdocs/sbom\-signing\-audit.md\fR (H2).
.TP
.B lvibe ci-smoke
.RI [ \-\-json | args ]
Repository smoke QA (\fBci\-smoke.sh\fR); \fB\-\-json\fR for paths and captured output — \fBdocs/ci\-qa\-hardening.md\fR (H3).
.TP
.B lvibe ci\-editor\-gate
.RI [ \-\-json | args ]
Editor vendoring gate (\fBci\-editor\-gate.sh\fR); \fB\-\-json\fR for paths and captured output — \fBdocs/ci\-qa\-hardening.md\fR (H3).
.TP
.B lvibe brand-paths
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-json ]
Canonical app icon paths; \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths — \fBdocs/brand\-assets.md\fR (H5).
.TP
.B lvibe product\-surface
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json ]
H8 product\-surface file paths; \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths — \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 12.
.TP
.B lvibe flatpak\-appimage
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json ]
H7 Flatpak/AppImage template paths; \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths — \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 13.
.TP
.B lvibe ide\-prereqs
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json | \-\-print\-closeout\-commands ]
§7.3 IDE paths / \fBVSCode\-linux\-*\fR state; \fB\-\-json\fR (\fBvscode_linux_build\fR, \fBvscode_linux_partial\fR, etc.); \fB\-\-print\-closeout\-commands\fR (\fBprobe\-vscode\-linux\-build.sh\fR; \fBprobe\_vscode\_linux\_build.py \-h\fR recovery; preflight, verify, status blocks, \fBbuild\-le\-vibe\-debs.sh \-\-with\-ide\fR when \fBready\fR; skips stack \fBdpkg\-buildpackage\fR until then; \fBpartial\fR / \fBabsent\fR: \fBpackaging/scripts/trigger\-le\-vibe\-ide\-linux\-compile.sh\fR, \fBpackaging/scripts/download\-vscodium\-linux\-compile\-artifact.sh\fR, \fBprint\-github\-linux\-compile\-artifact\-hint.sh\fR, \fBinstall\-vscodium\-linux\-tarball\-to\-editor\-vendor.sh\fR, \fBpackaging/scripts/print\-step14\-vscode\-linux\-bin\-files.sh\fR, \fBeditor/print\-ci\-tarball\-codium\-path.sh\fR 14.f; verify \fB\-\-json\fR: \fBdesktop_file_validate\fR; test host \fBmanual\-step14\-install\-smoke.sh \-\-json\fR: \fBdesktop_file_validate_on_path\fR; \fBmanual\-step14\-install\-smoke.sh \-\-verify\-only\fR, optional \fBdesktop\-file\-validate\fR) \-\- \fBeditor/BUILD.md\fR, \fBdocs/PM_DEB_BUILD_ITERATION.md\fR; \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 14.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/le\-vibe/
Configs, first\-run marker, welcome marker (\fB.welcome\-shown\fR), managed Ollama state,
\fBmodel\-decision.json\fR, \fBlock\-model.json\fR (concrete Ollama tag lock), \fBcontinue\-config.yaml\fR.
.TP
.I .lvibe/
Per\-project workspace memory hub \fBafter\fR you accept consent on first open (e.g. \fBlvibe .\fR); agent memory layout; add \fB.lvibe/\fR to \fB.gitignore\fR when that file exists. Summary: \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR le\-vibe\-setup\-continue (1),
.BR codium (1),
.BR ollama (1).
Full docs: \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
